50|$|An {{important}} {{property of}} a <b>gyrator</b> {{is that it}} inverts the current-voltage characteristic of an electrical component or network. In the case of linear elements, the impedance is also inverted. In other words, a <b>gyrator</b> can make a capacitive circuit behave inductively, a series LC circuit behave like a parallel LC circuit, and so on. It is primarily used in active filter design and miniaturization.|$|E
